# Project Structure Guide

This is a Next.js 15 application with TypeScript, Clerk authentication, and Convex backend, configured for Hebrew RTL support.

## Key Files and Directories

- **Main Entry Point**: [app/layout.tsx](mdc:app/layout.tsx) - Root layout with Hebrew RTL configuration
- **App Router**: [app/](mdc:app/) - Next.js 15 App Router file-based routing
- **Authentication**: [app/(auth)/](mdc:app/(auth)/) - Auth pages (sign-in, sign-up)
- **Components**: [components/](mdc:components/) - Reusable UI components
- **Convex Backend**: [convex/](mdc:convex/) - Backend functions and database schema
- **Configuration**: [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts), [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json), [biome.json](mdc:biome.json), [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts), [components.json](mdc:components.json)

## App Structure

- **Pages**: [app/page.tsx](mdc:app/page.tsx), [app/page1/page.tsx](mdc:app/page1/page.tsx), [app/page2/page.tsx](mdc:app/page2/page.tsx), [app/page3/page.tsx](mdc:app/page3/page.tsx)
- **Auth Pages**: [app/(auth)/sign-in/page.tsx](mdc:app/(auth)/sign-in/page.tsx), [app/(auth)/sign-up/page.tsx](mdc:app/(auth)/sign-up/page.tsx)
- **Components**: [components/Navbar.tsx](mdc:components/Navbar.tsx), [components/SignInModal.tsx](mdc:components/SignInModal.tsx)
- **Providers**: [components/providers/providers.tsx](mdc:components/providers/providers.tsx) - Clerk and Convex providers

## Key Technologies

- **Next.js 15**: React framework with App Router
- **TypeScript**: Type-safe JavaScript with strict mode
- **Clerk**: Authentication service
- **Convex**: Backend-as-a-service with real-time capabilities
- **Tailwind CSS v4**: Utility-first CSS framework with PostCSS
- **ShadCN UI**: Pre-built accessible components with Tailwind
- **Radix UI**: Accessible component primitives (used by ShadCN)
- **Biome**: Fast linter and formatter
- **Bun**: Package manager (preferred over npm/yarn)

## RTL/Hebrew Support

The app is configured for Hebrew RTL (Right-to-Left) text direction:
- `lang="he"` and `dir="rtl"` in root layout
- Hebrew metadata and descriptions
- RTL-aware component structure